Hospital reports that are valid at the SGK
How do I apply for disability?
Which are the hospitals from where I can get a health report?
For health council reports, it is sufficient to apply to the provincial social security directorates or social security centres.
The SGK will ask you to visit an educational and research hospital associated with the Ministry of Health, a University hospital (excluding private university and foundation hospitals) or a military hospital of the Turkish Armed Forces.
However, if those hospitals are not present in the province where you live, you may be sent to a fully established hospital run by the Ministry of Health.
Can I be sent to a private hospital?
