Grubb said that in India, apart from restrictions imposed by the Government on gold imports, the Indian Central Bank implemented measures to support the depreciating value of the rupee and preventing foreign currency outflows and said: "The nature of gold demand – restricting the retail demand level for gold – looks difficult and hence the demand can be met by unauthorized channels.
